[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    366[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe architecture-diagram infinite-loop and the prose-orchestration silence on [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mROUTED_TO_HUMAN_REVIEW[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m are the same gap surfaced in the main recipe that, in the Python companion, becomes the specific orchestrator bug of auto-delivering [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mREVIEW_REQUIRED[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m with [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mstatus = DELIVERED[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m. The code review flagged the Python-side instance as a WARNING; the main recipe's architecture is the upstream cause. Fixing the main recipe's diagram and walkthrough (A1) without fixing the Python companion's orchestrator is a half-measure; fixing the Python companion's orchestrator without updating the diagram and prose leaves the main recipe misleading future readers. The editor should treat this as a linked pair and update both in the same pass.[K
