[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    267[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│    delivered, patient response, escalations made)                │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    268[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│           │                                                      │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    269[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│           ▼                                                      │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    270[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│   [Outcome Capture]                                              │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    271[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│   (readmission events, ED visits, post-discharge mortality,      │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    272[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│    program graduation; linked to upstream alerts)                │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    273[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│           │                                                      │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    274[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│           ▼                                                      │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    275[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│   [Monitoring + Governance]                                      │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    276[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│   (subgroup performance, calibration drift, alert volume vs.     │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    277[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│    capacity, intervention success rates, equity audits)          │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    278[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│           │                                                      │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    279[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│           ▼                                                      │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    280[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│   [Periodic Retraining + Threshold Review]                       │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    281[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m│                                                                  │[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    282[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    283[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m```[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    284[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    285[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mIngest and normalization.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m RPM data flows from device-vendor APIs (BodyTrace, A[38;2;192;197;206m&[38;2;192;197;206mD Medical, iHealth, Withings, etc.) usually via webhook or pull. PRO data flows from the patient-facing app or SMS/IVR vendor. EHR events flow from the EHR integration platform (HL7, FHIR). Care management interactions flow from the care management tool. The normalizer produces a canonical patient event with a small number of event types (measurement, symptom report, ED visit, refill, outreach, escalation, etc.).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    286[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    287[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPost-discharge patient state store.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Every patient currently in the post-discharge monitoring program has a state record: enrollment date, condition cohort, discharge-time tier, current monitoring tier, last contact date, intervention history, and pointers to the trajectory history. The state store is the substrate the worklist UI reads.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    288[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    289[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mTrajectory history store.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Time-series of weights, blood pressures, glucoses, symptom scores, and the like. Retention covers multiple weeks for baseline computation. Per-patient indices for fast retrieval.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    290[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    291[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFeature engine.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Computes per-modality features (current value, last 3-day slope, last 7-day slope, deviation from baseline, missing-data indicator) and patient-level features (engagement decay, time since last contact, days post-discharge, condition cohort, discharge-time tier). For cold-start patients, feature values fall back to cohort priors.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    292[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    293[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mScoring service.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Hosts the per-modality anomaly detectors (control charts, residual-based detectors) and the composite scoring model (gradient-boosted trees on the engineered features). Produces calibrated scores and per-feature SHAP contributions for the explanation layer.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    294[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    295[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mWorklist builder.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Ranks patients by composite score, applies suppression rules (recently-contacted patients are de-prioritized; patients who are already in active intervention are tracked separately), de-duplicates across overlapping cohorts, and attaches the explanation and suggested next action to each row.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    296[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    297[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCare management workflow tools.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The product. The actual UI the care managers, transitions nurses, pharmacists, and providers interact with. Often a separate vendor system (Salesforce Health Cloud, Epic Healthy Planet, Innovaccer, Lumeris, custom-built) consuming the worklist data via API.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    298[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    299[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mIntervention capture.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Every outreach attempt, every contact, every intervention is recorded with timestamps. The capture data flows back to the scoring service for tier adjustment (a patient who just got a same-day visit is lower priority for the next 24 hours) and to the retraining pipeline as features.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    300[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    301[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mOutcome capture.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Readmissions, ED visits, deaths, and program graduations are captured from the EHR feed, the HIE, and (for ACO/risk-bearing arrangements) the claims feed. Outcomes are linked to alerts and interventions for label assembly.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    302[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    303[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mMonitoring and governance.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Subgroup performance dashboards, alert volume by team and tier, intervention success rates (call connected, intervention delivered, downstream outcome avoided), equity audits across demographic groups. The governance committee reviews these dashboards on a defined cadence (often monthly for clinical leadership, quarterly for executive review).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    304[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    305[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mRetraining and threshold review.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Quarterly is typical. Use accumulated outcome labels. Compare candidate models against current production. Subgroup performance check. Calibration check. Shadow deployment for a defined period before promotion. Threshold review independent of retraining: alert volume targets shift as care management capacity shifts.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    306[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    307[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m---[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    308[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    309[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m##[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mThe AWS Implementation[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    310[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    311[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhy These Services[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    312[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    313[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon API Gateway and AWS Lambda for RPM device webhook ingestion.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m RPM device vendors send measurements via webhook. API Gateway receives the webhook, Lambda validates and normalizes it, and the canonical event flows into the rest of the pipeline. For vendors that prefer pull-based integration, scheduled Lambdas pull from vendor APIs on the configured cadence.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    314[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    315[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Kinesis Data Streams (or Amazon SQS) for the canonical event stream.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The normalized canonical events flow through Kinesis (when ordering and replay matter) or SQS (when simpler queueing is sufficient). The cadence is much lower than Recipe 3.7 (a moderate-sized program might see thousands of events per day per few hundred patients, not millions); the simpler queue often suffices.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    316[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    317[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon DynamoDB for the patient state store.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Single-digit-millisecond reads on the current patient snapshot. Each enrolled patient is a record with current monitoring tier, recent values, engagement metrics, and intervention history pointers. DynamoDB streams trigger feature recomputation when state changes.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    318[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    319[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Timestream for the trajectory history store.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Patient-reported weights, blood pressures, glucoses, and symptom scores are time-series data. Timestream's purpose-built storage and query model fit naturally. Magnetic-tier retention covers the multi-week baseline window cost-effectively. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m TODO (TechWriter): verify the current HIPAA eligibility status of Amazon Timestream and the BAA coverage; some deployments may use DynamoDB or S3 with Athena instead. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    320[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    321[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS HealthLake for the longitudinal patient record.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m When the program needs FHIR-formatted patient records integrated with the wider health-system data, HealthLake provides storage, query, and integration. For programs with established FHIR infrastructure, HealthLake is a strong fit.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    322[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    323[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon SageMaker for model training, hosting, and feature management.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The composite scoring model trains as a SageMaker Training Job against retrospective data in S3, deploys to a SageMaker endpoint for daily scoring (batch transform is appropriate for daily cadence; real-time endpoint is appropriate for high-frequency rescoring on new data). SageMaker Feature Store keeps offline (training) and online (scoring) feature vectors consistent. SageMaker Clarify produces fairness reports across subgroups and per-prediction SHAP values.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    324[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    325[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon SageMaker Model Monitor.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Continuously monitors data drift, prediction drift, and (with labels) model quality. Critical for catching the gradual drift in patient population, intervention pattern, and device firmware that affects post-discharge programs.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    326[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    327[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Bedrock for explanation narratives and outreach script suggestions.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m SHAP values surface the technical drivers; Bedrock-hosted LLMs convert them and the patient context into care-manager-facing narratives ("This patient's weight has trended up 2.4 lbs over the last 3 days. They responded to symptom check-ins through Friday but not Saturday or Sunday. Their last care management contact was Wednesday. Suggested outreach: confirm weight trend, ask about diuretic adherence, ask about diet over the weekend, consider same-day clinic add-on.") Always with human review; the LLM is producing decision support, not decisions. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m TODO (TechWriter): confirm the set of HIPAA-eligible Bedrock foundation models as of the current year. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    328[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    329[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Comprehend Medical for free-text feature extraction.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Care management notes contain substantial signal in free text. Comprehend Medical extracts conditions, symptoms, medications, and concerns. Optional but useful when the care management interaction feed is text-rich.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    330[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    331[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS Step Functions for orchestration.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The daily scoring run, the worklist generation, and the periodic retraining are multi-step workflows. Step Functions handles orchestration with retry and error handling.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    332[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    333[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon EventBridge for routing.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Scoring outputs publish to EventBridge with patient context and tier. Subscribers include the worklist UI back end, the pharmacist review list back end, the provider escalation list, and the audit logger.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    334[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    335[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon API Gateway and AWS AppSync for the care management workflow back end.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The care management UI (whether built in-house or vendored) consumes the worklist via API. AppSync (GraphQL) is often a better fit when the UI needs flexible queries over patient state, intervention history, and trajectory data; API Gateway plus REST is fine for simpler integrations.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    336[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    337[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon OpenSearch Service for worklist audit and analytics.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Every score, every alert, every intervention, and every outcome is indexed in OpenSearch for governance queries, performance analytics, and ad-hoc clinical safety review. Data also flows to S3 for retraining.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    338[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    339[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon S3 for the data lake.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Historical RPM data, PRO data, EHR events, and outcome labels live here, partitioned by date and patient. Customer-managed KMS encryption. Used by SageMaker for training and Athena for ad-hoc analysis.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    340[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    341[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon QuickSight for governance dashboards.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Subgroup performance, intervention success rates, alert volume, capacity utilization, and program-level outcome metrics. The clinical leadership team and the program operations team consume these.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    342[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    343[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Athena for ad-hoc analysis.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Care managers, analysts, and the program team query the lake for ad-hoc questions ("how many patients in this cohort had at least one successful contact in the first week"). Athena over partitioned S3 is the cheap, flexible answer.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    344[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    345[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS HealthOmics or generic S3 for genomic data (rarely relevant).[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Most readmission programs do not use genomic data. Mentioned only for completeness; usually skip.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    346[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    347[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS End User Messaging or a third-party SMS/IVR vendor for patient outreach.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The outreach itself (SMS check-ins, IVR calls) is often delivered through specialist healthcare communication vendors (CipherHealth, GetWellNetwork, Memora Health, Cipher). For SMS-only, AWS End User Messaging (formerly Pinpoint SMS and Voice) works. The integration boundary matters: keep PHI in HIPAA-eligible services; the patient-facing channel needs a BAA.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    348[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    349[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon CloudWatch and AWS X-Ray.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Operational monitoring of the pipeline, scoring latency, end-to-end traces. Latency budgets matter less than Recipe 3.7 (the cadence is daily, not per-event), but data freshness matters: a worklist computed at 7 a.m. should reflect data through end-of-day yesterday plus any overnight events.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    350[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    351[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS CloudTrail.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Audit logging on every PHI-bearing store and every API call against the scoring service. Every score, every worklist generation, every intervention is logged.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    352[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
